65. dum edormiscat unum somnum, ‘ till she sleeps just one sleep.' Unum is used to justify paulisper. The general use of edormi-scere, edormire, is not to sleep out a sleep, but to sleep off the effects of wine. Rud. 2. 7. 28, A beo hinc ut edormiscam hanc crapulam ,· Ter.
